OL,3,CExplained: Why are Birmingham
OL,4,CAirport's night flights so
OL,5,Ccontroversial?
OL,7,FThe new cap means that, by 2026-27,
OL,8,Fthey'll be able to facilitate 7,600
OL,9,Fflights at night each year. 4,000 more
OL,10,Fflights than took off in 2022.
OL,12,FThat's equivalent to an average of 21
OL,13,Fper night, though the airport has said
OL,14,Fthe majority would take place between
OL,15,F11:30pm and 1am and 5 and 6am.
OL,17,FAt the moment Birmingham Airport
OL,18,Fcontributes 1.2bn to the Solihull
OL,19,Feconomy and 2.1 billion to the
OL,20,Fregional economy, according to
OL,21,Faviation consultancy York Aviation.
